Vallad to the Studios!  \n\nMarina's academic and environmental background spans two degrees and work as a mosquito biology lab technician, sea camp instructor, 7th grade science teacher, community garden coordinator and pediatric speech language pathologist.  All of which influence her delicate pressed-plant compositions.  \n\n\"My pieces begin with foraging and preserving a wide range of wild plants found throughout Brevard County.  I look for plants that tell a story - whether through their unexpected uses, familiarity, striking appearance, or their ability to convey the rich biodiversity of our local ecosystem.\n\nEach plant is pressed using a traditional flower press for up to two months.  I use quality, locally-sourced and repurposed frames and glass to reduce waste and add character.  Every arrangement is shaped by the distinct qualities of the plants and the natural landscapes they come from, along with the unique character of the frame.
